---
import PageShell from '../../components/PageShell.astro';
import CTABox from '../../components/CTABox.astro';
import ComparisonTable from '../../components/ComparisonTable.astro';

const tocItems = [
  { id: 'overview', text: 'Overview', level: 2 },
  { id: 'coverage-comparison', text: 'Coverage Comparison', level: 2 },
  { id: 'pricing', text: 'Pricing', level: 2 },
  { id: 'network-and-claims', text: 'Network and Claims', level: 2 },
  { id: 'who-should-choose', text: 'Who Should Choose Which', level: 2 },
  { id: 'verdict', text: 'Our Verdict', level: 2 },
];

const relatedLinks = [
  { title: 'SafetyWing Review', href: '/providers/safetywing' },
  { title: 'IMG Global Review', href: '/providers/img-global' },
  { title: 'Best Digital Nomad Insurance', href: '/best/digital-nomad-insurance' },
];

const coverageColumns = [
  { key: 'feature', header: 'Feature' },
  { key: 'safetywing', header: 'SafetyWing Nomad' },
  { key: 'img', header: 'IMG Global' },
];

const coverageRows = [
  { feature: 'Type', safetywing: 'Travel Medical', img: 'Health Insurance' },
  { feature: 'Maximum Coverage', safetywing: '$250,000', img: '$1M-$8M' },
  { feature: 'Deductible', safetywing: '$250 (fixed)', img: '$250-$10,000' },
  { feature: 'Outpatient Care', safetywing: 'Emergency only', img: 'Full coverage' },
  { feature: 'Mental Health', safetywing: 'Not covered', img: 'Included' },
  { feature: 'Maternity', safetywing: 'Not covered', img: 'Optional add-on' },
  { feature: 'Pre-existing', safetywing: 'Not covered', img: 'Underwritten' },
  { feature: 'Medical Evacuation', safetywing: '$100,000', img: 'Included' },
  { feature: 'US Coverage', safetywing: '30 days/90', img: 'Full (optional)' },
];

const pricingColumns = [
  { key: 'profile', header: 'Profile' },
  { key: 'safetywing', header: 'SafetyWing Nomad' },
  { key: 'img', header: 'IMG Silver' },
];

const pricingRows = [
  { profile: 'Age 30, ex-US', safetywing: '$45/4 weeks', img: '$100-150/mo' },
  { profile: 'Age 40, ex-US', safetywing: '$76/4 weeks', img: '$150-235/mo' },
  { profile: 'Age 50, ex-US', safetywing: '$117/4 weeks', img: '$250-350/mo' },
  { profile: 'Age 60, ex-US', safetywing: '$189/4 weeks', img: '$400-550/mo' },
];
---

<PageShell
  title="SafetyWing vs IMG Global"
  description="Compare SafetyWing and IMG Global side by side. Coverage, pricing, and which plan is right for budget-conscious nomads and expats."
  headline="SafetyWing vs IMG Global: Budget Options Compared"
  subheadline="Two popular budget-friendly options with very different approaches. Travel medical vs comprehensive health insurance—which fits your needs?"
  tocItems={tocItems}
  relatedLinks={relatedLinks}
  ctaButtonText="Get Quotes from Both"
  ctaButtonHref="/best/expat-health-insurance"
>
  <h2 id="overview">Overview</h2>
  <p>
    SafetyWing and IMG Global both appeal to budget-conscious travelers and expats, but they're fundamentally different products. Understanding this difference is critical before choosing.
  </p>

  <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-6 my-8">
    <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-3">SafetyWing Nomad Insurance</h3>
      <ul class="space-y-2 text-neutral-600">
        <li><strong>Type:</strong> Travel medical insurance</li>
        <li>Subscription-based (cancel anytime)</li>
        <li>Covers emergencies and acute illness</li>
        <li>$250,000 maximum coverage</li>
        <li>Simple, transparent pricing</li>
        <li>Popular with digital nomads</li>
      </ul>
    </div>
    <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-3">IMG Global</h3>
      <ul class="space-y-2 text-neutral-600">
        <li><strong>Type:</strong> Comprehensive health insurance</li>
        <li>Annual policy commitment</li>
        <li>Full health coverage including routine care</li>
        <li>Up to $8 million maximum</li>
        <li>Flexible deductible options</li>
        <li>30+ years in the industry</li>
      </ul>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="bg-amber-50 border border-amber-200 rounded-lg p-6 my-6">
    <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-amber-900 mb-2">Critical Distinction</h3>
    <p class="text-amber-800">
      <strong>SafetyWing Nomad Insurance is travel medical insurance</strong>—it covers emergencies and unexpected illness while traveling. <strong>IMG Global is actual health insurance</strong>—it covers ongoing healthcare, routine visits, and comprehensive medical needs. These are not equivalent products despite both being "international insurance."
    </p>
  </div>

  <CTABox
    title="Compare Both Providers"
    description="Get quotes from SafetyWing and IMG Global for your situation."
    buttonText="Get Free Quotes"
    buttonHref="/best/expat-health-insurance"
    variant="highlight"
  />

  <h2 id="coverage-comparison">Coverage Comparison</h2>
  <p>
    The coverage gap between these two options is significant. SafetyWing covers emergencies; IMG covers your health.
  </p>

  <div class="my-8 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg overflow-hidden">
    <ComparisonTable columns={coverageColumns} rows={coverageRows} />
  </div>

  <p>
    <strong>Key differences:</strong>
  </p>
  <ul>
    <li>SafetyWing's $250K limit is low for serious illness (cancer treatment alone can exceed this)</li>
    <li>IMG covers routine doctor visits, prescriptions, and preventive care—SafetyWing doesn't</li>
    <li>Mental health coverage is only available with IMG</li>
    <li>SafetyWing has no pre-existing condition coverage at all; IMG underwrites them individually</li>
    <li>IMG offers 50% deductible waiver for treatment outside the US—a meaningful cost saver</li>
  </ul>

  <h3>SafetyWing Remote Health Alternative</h3>
  <p>
    SafetyWing also offers <strong>Remote Health</strong>, which is comprehensive health insurance (not travel medical). Remote Health competes more directly with IMG, with coverage up to $10M. If you want SafetyWing's subscription approach but need real health insurance, Remote Health is worth considering at $100-700/month depending on age and deductible.
  </p>

  <h2 id="pricing">Pricing</h2>
  <p>
    SafetyWing is cheaper—but you're buying less coverage. Compare prices carefully and consider what you're getting.
  </p>

  <div class="my-8 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg overflow-hidden">
    <ComparisonTable columns={pricingColumns} rows={pricingRows} />
  </div>

  <p>
    <strong>Notes on pricing:</strong>
  </p>
  <ul>
    <li>SafetyWing's pricing is straightforward: age-based, billed every 4 weeks</li>
    <li>IMG pricing varies by plan tier, deductible, and coverage area</li>
    <li>IMG's $5,000+ deductible options can reduce premiums significantly</li>
    <li>Monthly payment with IMG adds 20%—pay annually if possible</li>
    <li>SafetyWing has no commitment—cancel anytime. IMG is annual.</li>
  </ul>

  <div class="bg-blue-50 border border-blue-200 rounded-lg p-6 my-6">
    <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-blue-900 mb-2">Cost Per Coverage Dollar</h3>
    <p class="text-blue-800">
      SafetyWing costs less, but provides $250K maximum coverage. IMG's Silver plan costs more but provides $5M coverage with full health benefits. If you're healthy and just need emergency coverage while traveling, SafetyWing offers good value. If you need actual healthcare, IMG is the better investment.
    </p>
  </div>

  <CTABox
    title="Get Your Actual Price"
    description="See what each option would cost for your specific situation."
    buttonText="Get a Quote"
    buttonHref="/best/expat-health-insurance"
  />

  <h2 id="network-and-claims">Network and Claims</h2>

  <h3>Provider Networks</h3>
  <p>
    <strong>IMG Global</strong> offers direct billing with many providers worldwide. Their Travel Intelligence feature helps locate nearby providers, and they have relationships with hospitals across 100+ countries.
  </p>
  <p>
    <strong>SafetyWing</strong> coordinates with hospitals for major emergencies but most claims are reimbursement-based. Their network is less developed than traditional insurers.
  </p>

  <h3>Claims Process</h3>
  <p>
    <strong>IMG:</strong> Online and app-based claims submission. Processing can take several weeks—a common complaint in reviews. Documentation is important.
  </p>
  <p>
    <strong>SafetyWing:</strong> Simple online claims portal. Mixed reviews—straightforward for small claims, but some users report delays and denials requiring appeals.
  </p>

  <h3>Customer Service</h3>
  <p>
    <strong>IMG:</strong> 24/7 support in 18 languages, in-house nurses and case managers. More traditional insurance service.
  </p>
  <p>
    <strong>SafetyWing:</strong> Email and chat support during business hours. No 24/7 phone line. More startup-style support.
  </p>

  <h2 id="who-should-choose">Who Should Choose Which</h2>

  <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-6 my-8">
    <div class="bg-primary-50 border border-primary-200 rounded-lg p-6">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-3">Choose SafetyWing If:</h3>
      <ul class="space-y-2 text-neutral-600">
        <li>You're young and healthy (under 40)</li>
        <li>You only need emergency/accident coverage</li>
        <li>You're testing the nomad lifestyle short-term</li>
        <li>You want no commitment—cancel anytime</li>
        <li>You're on a tight budget</li>
        <li>You have access to affordable local healthcare</li>
      </ul>
    </div>
    <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-3">Choose IMG Global If:</h3>
      <ul class="space-y-2 text-neutral-600">
        <li>You need actual health insurance, not just emergency coverage</li>
        <li>You want higher coverage limits ($1M-$8M)</li>
        <li>Mental health coverage matters to you</li>
        <li>You may need routine care or prescriptions</li>
        <li>You're over 40 or have health concerns</li>
        <li>You want flexible deductible options</li>
      </ul>
    </div>
  </div>

  <h2 id="verdict">Our Verdict</h2>
  <p>
    SafetyWing and IMG Global serve different needs. They're not really competitors—they're different product categories.
  </p>
  <p>
    <strong>SafetyWing Nomad Insurance</strong> is excellent for what it is: affordable emergency coverage for healthy travelers who want flexibility. If you're 25, have no health issues, and just want a safety net while you hop between countries, it's hard to beat the value and simplicity.
  </p>
  <p>
    <strong>IMG Global</strong> is the choice when you need real health insurance. If you're planning to live abroad long-term, have any health conditions, are over 40, or want peace of mind that you're covered for more than just emergencies, IMG provides that comprehensive coverage.
  </p>
  <p>
    The price difference reflects the coverage difference. SafetyWing isn't "cheap IMG"—it's a different product. Choose based on what you actually need, not just the monthly cost.
  </p>

  <CTABox
    title="Ready to Decide?"
    description="Compare quotes from both providers based on your specific needs."
    buttonText="Compare Plans Now"
    buttonHref="/best/expat-health-insurance"
    variant="highlight"
  />

  <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6 mt-8">
    <p class="text-sm text-neutral-600">
      <strong>Disclaimer:</strong> This comparison is for informational purposes only. Prices, coverage, and plan details change. We are not insurance brokers. Verify all information with the providers before purchasing.
    </p>
  </div>
</PageShell>
